      • createTransaction

        public Cancelable createTransaction(java.util.List<? extends ch.decent.sdk.model.operation.BaseOperation> operations,
                                    org.threeten.bp.Duration expiration,
                                    Callback<ch.decent.sdk.model.Transaction> callback)

        create unsigned transaction

        Parameters:
        operations - operations to include in transaction
        expiration - transaction expiration in seconds, after the expiry the transaction is removed from recent pool and will be dismissed if not included in DCore block
        callback - a callback object that asynchronously receives the result value or error
        Returns:
        a request handler object which can be used to cancel the request

      • get

        public Cancelable get(java.lang.String trxId,
                      Callback<ch.decent.sdk.model.ProcessedTransaction> callback)

        This method will return the transaction for the given ID or it will return exception ObjectNotFoundException. The ID can be retrieved from class Transaction or class TransactionConfirmation objects.

        Note: By default these objects are not tracked, the transaction_history_plugin must be loaded for these objects to be maintained. Just because it is not known does not mean it wasn't included in the DCore.

        Parameters:
        trxId - transaction id
        callback - a callback object that asynchronously receives the result value or error
        Returns:
        a request handler object which can be used to cancel the request
        See Also:
        exception ObjectNotFoundException, class Transaction, class TransactionConfirmation
